sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GG95
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains two fluorescent protein coding sites (for RFP and GFP) and was assembled using Golden Gate Assembly. To make plasmid, parts were taken from iGEM Registry (BBa_J04450 (RFP) and BBa_I13522 (GFP)) and assembled to make new part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Laura Xinyu Chen, Melody Wu, Katie Maruna
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The GFP and RFP parts come from the iGEM GFP & RFP coding devices.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is one part of a series of parts, each with different orientations of GFP and RFP. It was used to test the expression of fluorescence under different conditions of GFP and RFP.
